comments: Smith Jr. (HOU) brings his right hand forward prior to marginal contact occurring with DeRozan's (CHI) off-arm as the pick approaches.
DeRozan (CHI) brings his left hand toward Smith Jr.'s (HOU) front and marginal contact occurs as DeRozan releases away.
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in Smith Jr.'s (HOU) path and does not deliver illegal contact as he sets the pick.

LaVine (CHI) leads with his left arm and initiates contact with Sengun's (HOU) head and neck area during the driving shot attempt. After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that the contact did not meet the criteria for a flagrant foul.
Caruso (CHI) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Green's (HOU) left arm after the release.
DeRozan (CHI) engages and disengages with Smith Jr. (HOU), and marginal contact occurs after the release of the jump shot attempt.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Whitmore (HOU) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Vucevic (CHI) is turning slightly prior to marginal contact occurring with Whitmore (HOU) after Whitmore commits to going under the pick.
VanVleet's (HOU) left arm comes up toward Vucevic's (CHI) right shoulder and marginal contact occurs as they each pursue the rebound.
LaVine (CHI) moves laterally into Green's (HOU) path and is not in a legal guarding position when body contact occurs after Green's gather.
Caruso (CHI) establishes himself in Smith Jr.'s (HOU) path and does not deliver illegal contact as he sets the screen.

Referees reviewed the loose ball foul called on Green (HOU) for contact with DeRozan (CHI) and determined that it occurred before the expiration of the shot clock.  During their review, referees also determined that DeRozan flopped (which is explained separately in non-unsportsmanlike technical commentary). Since the foul itself was not a reviewable matter under this replay trigger, subsequent to the referee's explanation of their decision, HOU initiated a coach's challenge on the foul itself, which was unsuccessful because, while DeRozan flopped to exaggerate the contact, Green still pushed him by extending his forearm and hand into his side.

A non-unsportsmanlike technical foul was called on DeRozan (CHI) for flopping. DeRozan's reaction to Green's (HOU) contact was determined to be overtly theatrical, and not commensurate with the degree of contact.
Caruso (CHI) establishes himself in Smith Jr.'s (HOU) path and does not deliver illegal contact as the defensive switch simultaneously occurs during the pick.
Sengun (HOU) establishes himself in Caruso's (CHI) path and does not deliver illegal contact as he sets the pick.
LaVine (CHI) and DeRozan (CHI) each legally contest Sengun's (HOU) layup attempt.
Smith Jr. (HOU) brushes DeRozan's (CHI) right arm and marginal contact occurs as DeRozan starts his upward shooting motion.
LaVine (CHI) and Smith Jr. (HOU) engage and disengage with one another, and marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
LaVine (CHI) jumps to Smith Jr.'s (HOU) side and would avoid Smith Jr. if he did not slightly extend his left arm and leg to initiate the marginal contact after the release of the jump shot attempt.
Sengun (HOU) extends slightly as he is firming up over his right foot in LaVine's (CHI) path and he does not deliver illegal contact during the pick.
Vucevic (CHI) initiates contact with Green's (HOU) left arm prior to the release of his driving shot attempt, which is subsequently affected.
Caruso (CHI) moves forward into VanVleet (HOU) and initiates body contact that affects VanVleet's SQBR as he dribbles toward the pick.

Vucevic (CHI) aligns to move alongside Sengun's (HOU) path and marginal contact occurs with Sengun's left side after his gather. White (CHI) then establishes himself in Sengun's path and absorbs the marginal contact that occurs thereafter.
Vucevic (CHI) cleanly blocks Whitmore's (HOU) dunk attempt.
LaVine (CHI) establishes his left foot as his pivot and slides it as he comes to a stop on the perimeter.
Green (HOU) turns slightly and marginal body contact occurs with LaVine's (CHI) front prior to LaVine making the pass.
VanVleet (HOU) does not inbound the ball within five seconds.
Caruso (CHI) moves somewhat laterally prior to marginal body contact occurring with VanVleet (HOU) at the end of the drive.
Sengun (HOU) brings his right arm forward and marginal contact occurs with Vucevic's (CHI) right arm/side as Vucevic secures the rebound.
LaVine (CHI) brings his right arm forward prior to marginal contact occurring with Sengun's (HOU) slightly extended off-arm in transition.
Caruso (CHI) brushes VanVleet's (HOU) left side and marginal contact occurs as VanVleet drives toward the lane.
Smith Jr. (HOU) moves down the lane and incidental contact with White (CHI) occurs off-ball. Smith Jr. does not deliver the contact.
Sengun (HOU) commits a take foul on LaVine (CHI). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
VanVleet (HOU) commits a take foul on Caruso (CHI). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
LaVine (CHI) legally contests VanVleet's (HOU) jump shot attempt.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: VanVleet (HOU) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
